ROBERT EARL NICKEL v. ELENORA NICKEL. Decided June 11th, 1926.

The cause was argued before Bowd, C. J., Pattisow, Urwer, Adkiws, Oeeutt, Digges, Paeke, and Walsh, JJ.

J. Philip Roman and Walter C. Capper, for the appellant. Howard Galbreth and Harry R. Donnelly, for the appellee. Adkins, J.,

delivered the opinion of the Court, affirming the decree in part and reversing it in part, and dismissing both the original and cross-bills, with costs to the appellee.
